basic commands
    - cat 
        which sends file content to stdout.
    - ls 
         % ls -l
        total 3
        -rw-rw-rw-   1 john     1659    386 Feb  3 08:15 groceries
        -rw-r--r--   1 john     1659     97 Mar 10 23:46 schedule
        -rw-------   1 john     1659    123 Mar 11 13:39 todo
        1 file type
        2 permission
            1 permission to owner
            2 permission to group
            3 permission to other
        3 number of links
        4 owner
        5 group
        6 size of file
        7 month
        8 date
        9 time
        10 file name       
        
    - date
        displays system time & date
    - logname
        user name
    - cal
        calendar
    - 
    
    
file/ directory  operations

    - touch 
        create normal file with permission "rw-rw-r--"
    - cp 
        copies file/ directory ( use '-r' option).
    - mv
        move or rename file / directory ( use '-r' option).
    - rm 
        copies file/ directory ( use '-r' option).
    - pwd
        displays current working directory.
    - cd 
        change directory.
    - mkdir 
        create new directory
    - file
        gives file information.
    - chmod
        change file/ directory permission's.
        
        
        
        
    